{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id80d29b8e-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s11102"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"11102"},"text":"§ 11102.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Sense of Congress","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"It is the sense of Congress that, during the five-year period beginning with 1996, executive agencies should achieve each year through improvements in information resources management by the agency—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id80d29b8f-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s11102/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" at least a five percent decrease in the cost (in constant fiscal year 1996 dollars) incurred by the agency in operating and maintaining information technology; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id80d29b90-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c","identifier":"/us/usc/t40/s11102/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" a five percent increase in the efficiency of the agency operations.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id80d29b91-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/217"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–217","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2002-08-21"},"text":"Aug. 21, 2002","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/116/1236"},"text":"116 Stat. 1236","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id80d29b92-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"id80d29b93-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf